{"TopicId":147876,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[KSP 1.3.1] Bon Voyage 0.13.2.1 - Make your wheels rolling! 2017-10-15","CreatedByName":"RealGecko","CreatedById":162682,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T19:23:51Z","PageNum":13,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-19T22:18:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223027214\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492637694\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150755\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DeltaDizzy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, DeltaDizzy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it work with boats?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sure it doesn\u0027t--if you don\u0027t have all your wheels on the ground it won\u0027t move.\u00A0 (Which I find annoying, so long as you have three on the ground that should be enough.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-20T00:18:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223027264\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492640317\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157006\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Loren Pechtel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Loren Pechtel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sure it doesn\u0027t--if you don\u0027t have all your wheels on the ground it won\u0027t move.\u00A0 (Which I find annoying, so long as you have three on the ground that should be enough.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt doesn\u0027t check for \u0027all\u0027 - I have an eight-wheel rover that\u0027s designed with six on the ground during normal operations, and the other two for getting itself unstuck, and it works fine with that.\u00A0 I wonder what the check is.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do believe it has to be \u0027landed\u0027 however, not \u0027splashed down\u0027.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DeltaDizzy","CreatedById":150755,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-20T20:04:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223027380\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492647506\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DStaal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 hours ago, DStaal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do believe it has to be \u0027landed\u0027 however, not \u0027splashed down\u0027.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell consider this a request for a boat version then\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-20T21:33:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150755-deltadizzy/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150755\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150755-deltadizzy/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DeltaDizzy\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157006-loren-pechtel/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022157006\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157006-loren-pechtel/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Loren Pechtel\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155685-dstaal/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155685\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155685-dstaal/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DStaal\u003C/a\u003E I had finally time to check code. At least four operable wheels must be touching ground, at least two wheels must be active and a situation must be LANDED.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Loren Pechtel","CreatedById":157006,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-20T21:53:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223028429\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492724023\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168379\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022maja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, maja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150755-deltadizzy/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150755\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150755-deltadizzy/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DeltaDizzy\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157006-loren-pechtel/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022157006\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/157006-loren-pechtel/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Loren Pechtel\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155685-dstaal/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155685\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155685-dstaal/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DStaal\u003C/a\u003E I had finally time to check code. At least four operable wheels must be touching ground, at least two wheels must be active and a situation must be LANDED.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChange request:\u00A0 Could you make that 3 wheels?\u00A0 I don\u0027t see any exploits there and the current rule means it often tells you no for no good reason when you\u0027re sitting on uneven ground.\u00A0 It also means it can\u0027t control a tricycle--something I have built a fair number of.\u00A0 (Admittedly, only early on with airplane wheels and with jet propulsion.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd can we have back the old menu that goes away when we go to the world view to select the target location?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-04-20T21:56:07Z\u0022 title=\u002204/20/2017 09:56  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EApril 20, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Loren Pechtel\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-20T22:10:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223028453\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221492725193\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022157006\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Loren Pechtel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Loren Pechtel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChange request:\u00A0 Could you make that 3 wheels?\u00A0 I don\u0027t see any exploits there and the current rule means it often tells you no for no good reason when you\u0027re sitting on uneven ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd can we have back the old menu that goes away when we go to the world view to select the target location?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not author of this mod. I have copy of the code, because I wanted to add MKS Power Pack as a power source (RealGecko has there \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Umbra Space Industries (a collection of mods)\u0022\u003EUSI\u003C/abbr\u003E reactors only).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat change is of course possible, but I will not post link to the dll here without permission \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m considering to maintain this mod, because there are few things which can be improved, if \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162682\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RealGecko\u003C/a\u003E don\u0027t have time to do this, but it\u0027s on him to decide.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Blackline","CreatedById":159475,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-23T11:05:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDiscriminating behaviour, give tiny rovers a chance!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022PE6taOQ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/PE6taOQ.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJoke aside, are there any plans for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E integration?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hakuhonoo","CreatedById":177276,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-29T09:56:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi there!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have issue with your mod, but I wanna run it badly \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is screenshot \u003Ca href=\u0022http://prntscr.com/f25v1p\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://prntscr.com/f25v1p\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPower production is 0 with any vehicle. This one or with Buffalo or with any else...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-04-29T15:38:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223038654\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221493459764\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022177276\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hakuhonoo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Hakuhonoo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi there!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have issue with your mod, but I wanna run it badly \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is screenshot \u003Ca href=\u0022http://prntscr.com/f25v1p\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://prntscr.com/f25v1p\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPower production is 0 with any vehicle. This one or with Buffalo or with any else...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you tried to press System check or Poehali button?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"aluc24","CreatedById":152712,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-01T20:28:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162682\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RealGecko\u003C/a\u003E , would it be possible to turn off the Bon Voyage controller for a vessel when it is terminated? Because right now, the control window still tracks debris that has the BV module, and it really clutters the window!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"-MadMan-","CreatedById":22353,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-04T07:40:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223038654\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221493459764\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022177276\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hakuhonoo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 29.04.2017 at 2:56 PM, Hakuhonoo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPower production is 0 with any vehicle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have Kerbalism?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#525252;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0026amp;referrer=http%253A%252F%252Fforum.kerbalspaceprogram.com%252Findex.php%253F%252Ftopic%252F147876-ksp-122-bon-voyage-0120-make-your-wheels-rolling-2017-03-18%252F\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0022 style=\u0022color:#ad1457;\u0022 title=\u0022Go to RealGecko\u0027s profile\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003ERealGecko\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0can you add option\u00A0\u0022Disable power production check\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Carrot","CreatedById":154743,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-06T00:56:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi again how to set a waypoint now? I can\u0027t find a way to do it \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-06T01:56:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223046530\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494032182\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154743\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Carrot\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n58 minutes ago, Carrot said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi again how to set a waypoint now? I can\u0027t find a way to do it \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWarypoints are a stock feature, I believe, so there should be some way to set them in stock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI find a combination of ScanSat and Waypoint Manager works well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/94432-12x-waypoint-manager-v262-2017-01-25/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-07T22:10:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI stumbled across some interesting behavior recently...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hooked up a Bon Voyage-enabled rover to a base via \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E pipes, left the scene, and quit KSP. \u00A0When I came back, only that base was listed in the Bon Voyage control panel, none of my other rovers were listed - even visiting them, restarting Bon Voyage, and leaving the scene/quitting wouldn\u0027t bring them back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, they came back when I unlinked the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E pipes, quit KSP and came back. \u00A0I did have to visit each one before it would start moving again, but they appeared to remember where they were supposed to be moving to and that they were moving.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"aluc24","CreatedById":152712,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-09T16:01:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223044434\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221493883636\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002222353\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022-MadMan-\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 5/4/2017 at 10:40 AM, -MadMan- said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you have Kerbalism?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n@\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#525252;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0026amp;referrer=http%253A%252F%252Fforum.kerbalspaceprogram.com%252Findex.php%253F%252Ftopic%252F147876-ksp-122-bon-voyage-0120-make-your-wheels-rolling-2017-03-18%252F\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022 style=\u0022color:#ad1457;\u0022 title=\u0022Go to RealGecko\u0027s profile\u0022\u003ERealGecko\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0can you add option\u00A0\u0022Disable power production check\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have Kerbalism too, and my solar power production is always 0. How do I fix this so I can use BV?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-11T15:09:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223048482\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494195008\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155685\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DStaal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8. 5. 2017 at 0:10 AM, DStaal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI stumbled across some interesting behavior recently...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hooked up a Bon Voyage-enabled rover to a base via \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E pipes, left the scene, and quit KSP. \u00A0When I came back, only that base was listed in the Bon Voyage control panel, none of my other rovers were listed - even visiting them, restarting Bon Voyage, and leaving the scene/quitting wouldn\u0027t bring them back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, they came back when I unlinked the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E pipes, quit KSP and came back. \u00A0I did have to visit each one before it would start moving again, but they appeared to remember where they were supposed to be moving to and that they were moving.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223050650\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494345693\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152712\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022aluc24\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 9. 5. 2017 at 6:01 PM, aluc24 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have Kerbalism too, and my solar power production is always 0. How do I fix this so I can use BV?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRealGecko is off since April 30. It\u0027s his mod, but I see what I can do unofficially. Probably next week, because I\u0027m off for this weekend.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"aluc24","CreatedById":152712,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-11T16:53:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223053231\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494515373\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168379\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022maja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, maja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRealGecko is off since April 30. It\u0027s his mod, but I see what I can do unofficially. Probably next week, because I\u0027m off for this weekend.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you! Will be waiting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-15T16:37:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155685-dstaal/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155685\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155685-dstaal/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DStaal\u003C/a\u003E Could you replicate it with stock, BV, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and provide a save? I can\u0027t replicate it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DStaal","CreatedById":155685,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-15T18:00:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223057407\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494866275\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168379\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022maja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, maja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155685-dstaal/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022155685\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/155685-dstaal/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DStaal\u003C/a\u003E Could you replicate it with stock, BV, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and provide a save? I can\u0027t replicate it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll see if I can re-create it.\u00A0 It was a weird situation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-16T08:45:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152712-aluc24/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022152712\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152712-aluc24/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@aluc24\u003C/a\u003E Kerbalism changes how EC production is handled, which breaks the BV checks. BV is incompatible with Kerbalism at the moment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"aluc24","CreatedById":152712,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-16T14:07:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223058211\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494924302\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168379\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022maja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, maja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152712-aluc24/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022152712\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/152712-aluc24/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@aluc24\u003C/a\u003E Kerbalism changes how EC production is handled, which breaks the BV checks. BV is incompatible with Kerbalism at the moment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe BV\u0027s EC production could be disabled until a compatibility bridge is built? It sucks to leave these rovers roving overnight only to find them crashed in the morning \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maja","CreatedById":168379,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-16T15:05:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223058346\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494943646\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152712\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022aluc24\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, aluc24 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe BV\u0027s EC production could be disabled until a compatibility bridge is built? It sucks to leave these rovers roving overnight only to find them crashed in the morning \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem with Kerbalism is, that it\u0027s zeroing charge rate value of solar panels and doing different EC production computations then stock system. I don\u0027t know right now, if and when this can be solved.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDisabling the EC check for Kerbalism users only is possible option.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"aluc24","CreatedById":152712,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-16T15:06:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223058379\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147876\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221494947115\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022168379\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022maja\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, maja said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe problem with Kerbalism is, that it\u0027s zeroing charge rate value of solar panels and doing different EC production computations then stock system. I don\u0027t know right now, if and when this can be solved.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDisabling the EC check for Kerbalism users only is possible option.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, if it\u0027s possible, maybe disabling that EC check for Kerbalism could be a quick\u0026amp;dirty fix until a more permanent one is found?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ShotgunNinja","CreatedById":159391,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-17T12:50:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nApologies guys, the next version of Kerbalism should solve the issue (I hope!). Meanwhile you can grab the updated dll \u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ShotgunNinja/Kerbalism/raw/master/GameData/Kerbalism/Kerbalism.dll\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PT","CreatedById":154223,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-05-17T13:08:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd to think that all that time I was watching StarTrek while \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Mechjeb (mod)\u0022\u003EMJ\u003C/abbr\u003E had the wheel at 4x warp \u0026gt;.\u0026lt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}